# Git commits

When making git commits in this project:

- **Do not** add Cursor, "cursor agent", or any AI/agent reference to commit messages, author, committer, or sign-off.
- Use the **repository's configured git user** (e.g. `git config user.name` / `user.email`) for author and committer. Do not set author/committer to anything that includes "Cursor" or "agent".
- Write **neutral commit messages** that describe the code change only (e.g. "Add X", "Fix Y"), with no mention of who or what suggested the change.
- Do not add `Co-authored-by`, `Signed-off-by`, or similar lines that reference Cursor or an agent.

This keeps the git history showing only the human developer.

